 whole theory of banking, the basic core of how banking =0Aworks, is that a=
 lot of people don=E2=80=99t pay attention to the interest rate on =0Atheir=
 bank accounts, so banks can pay them below-market rates. This is not a =0A=
minor peccadillo of nasty bankers; this is not a little malfeasance at the =
=0Aperiphery of a basically customer-centric industry; this is not =E2=80=
=9Coh those =0Asneaky bankers, trying to keep deposit rates low even as the=
 Fed raises rates.=E2=80=9D =0AThis is what bankingis. =E2=80=9CBanks can k=
