plaint says that Capital One deceived customers =E2=80=9Cby failing to fulf=
ill the consumer expectations it created,=E2=80=9D which is not exactly lyi=
ng. It=E2=80=99s stuff like this:</p> <blockquote> <p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">Between 2013 and 2019, Capital One marketed 360 Savings as a =E2=80=9C=
high interest=E2=80=9D online savings account with =E2=80=9Cgreat rates.=E2=
=80=9D</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Consumers reasonably understand =E2=
=80=9Chigh interest=E2=80=9D savings accounts to refer to a specific type o=
f savings product that is distinct from =E2=80=9Ctraditional=E2=80=9D savin=
gs accounts in at least one significant way: =E2=80=9CHigh interest=E2=80=
=9D savings accounts have interest rates that are many times higher than =
=E2=80=9Ctraditional=E2=80=9D savings account rates. =E2=80=A6</p> <p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Thus, although Capital One sets the 360 Savings intere=
st rate and, per its account disclosures, can change the rate at its discre=
tion, it was reasonable for consumers to interpret the Bank=E2=80=99s repre=
sentations about the 360 Savings rate to mean that the Bank would use its d=
iscretion=C2=A0to ensure that the rate was at a level that fulfilled the pr=
omises described above.</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It was reasonable =
for consumers to expect that the Bank=E2=80=99s representations about the 3=
60 Savings rate would remain true over the entire time period that 360 Savi=
ngs accountholders held their accounts.</p> </blockquote> <p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">It was=3F Why=3F In 2020, when it launched 360 Performance Savi=
ngs, Capital One=C2=A0<em>stopped=C2=A0</em>saying this stuff about 360 Sav=
ings. (And started saying it about 360 Performance Savings, I guess.) It is=
 probably=C2=A0<em>true=C2=A0</em>that a lot of depositors opened accounts =
in like 2013, thinking =E2=80=9Cah, Capital One tells me that the interest =
rate on this account is =E2=80=98great,=E2=80=99 so I will go ahead and ass=
ume that the interest rate on this account will remain =E2=80=98great=E2=80=
=99 forever.=E2=80=9D Maybe it=E2=80=99s even reasonable, out of context. I=
